cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below."
authors:
  - family-names: "Hiwase"
    given-names: "Uday"
    affiliation: "Indiana University"
title: "SENTINEL-RL: Offloading Topological Reasoning from LLM Agents in the Security Operations Center"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-04-28
url: "https://github.com/UdayIND/Uday-Independent-Study-Prv"
repository-code: "https://github.com/UdayIND/Uday-Independent-Study-Prv"
abstract: >-
  A four-plane neuro-symbolic agentic SOC that offloads topological reasoning
  from an LLM onto a heterogeneous graph attention network (HetGAT) encoder
  and a PPO-trained reinforcement learning policy. Evaluated end-to-end on
  the LANL 24M-edge authentication benchmark: 14.2-minute ingestion,
  2.45s alert latency, 0.91 precision and 0.87 recall, with a 6.3s median
  detect-to-contain loop.
keywords:
  - reinforcement-learning
  - graph-neural-networks
  - cybersecurity
  - security-operations-center
  - neuro-symbolic-ai
  - threat-detection
  - lateral-movement
  - ppo
  - neo4j
